Note : function with Property : Remember Function are just object that can be invoked . 



I% Prototypal Nature in javascript : 
    a% Classical 
    b% Pseudo-classical 
    c% Functional 

example of functional inheritance Pattern 
var user = function( ops )
{

return { firstName : ops.name || "john"
        ,lastName : ops.vorname || "doe"
        ,email   : ops.email || "dufilsfabrice@googlemail.com"
        ,name   : function(){ return this.firstName + this.lastName }
    }
}

